This paper deals with the formal semantics of functional logic programming languages, which falls under the category of programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also discusses the concept of full abstraction, which is related to logic and semantics (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of formal semantics as a guide for software development tools, which is related to software engineering (cs.SE). The paper specifically focuses on the family of modern functional logic languages, which could fall under the sub-category of functional programming (cs.FL). Finally, the paper discusses the properties of the CRWL semantic framework, which could be related to machine learning (cs.LG).
